00:05:03,450 --> 00:05:04,480
坦吉乐

43
00:05:04,620 --> 00:05:08,670
精华地段-拉斯维加斯，十年前
THE STRIP - LAS VEGAS TEN YEARS EARLIER

44
00:05:11,460 --> 00:05:12,490
谁抗拒的了？
SAM: Who could resist?

45
00:05:12,630 --> 00:05:15,340
在别处，我只是个登记赛马的一个赌徒…
Anywhere else, I was a bookie, a gambler...

46
00:05:15,470 --> 00:05:18,750
老是得小心翼翼，成天被条子们骚扰
always looking over my shoulder, hassled by cops, day and night.

47
00:05:18,890 --> 00:05:20,800
但在这儿，我可是罗斯坦先生
But here, I'm Mr. Rothstein.

48
00:05:20,930 --> 00:05:23,600
不但不偷鸡摸狗，还管间赌场
I'm not only legitimate, but running a casino.

49
00:05:23,680 --> 00:05:26,440
那就像是将梦想换为现金
And that's like selling people dreams for cash.

50
00:05:27,690 --> 00:05:31,600
我聘任了赌场的一个老朋友 比利雪伯当经理，然后开始工作
I hired an old casino pal, Billy Sherbert, as my manager, and went to work.

51
00:05:31,900 --> 00:05:35,320
这是负责牌室的罗尼
And this is Ronnie, who takes care of the card room.

52
00:05:37,990 --> 00:05:40,950
像我们这种人 拉斯维加斯洗去了我们的罪孽
SAM: For guys like me, Las Vegas washes away your sins.

53
00:05:41,080 --> 00:05:43,070
像是道德洗车场一样
It's like a morality car wash.

54
00:05:43,210 --> 00:05:46,660
它对我们的效用就像法国露德 对驼背和残障的人一样
It does for us what Lourdes does for humpbacks and cripples.

55
00:05:53,590 --> 00:05:55,720
不但让我们重见天日…
SAM: And along with making us legit...

56
00:05:56,220 --> 00:05:58,800
还带来了现金，数不尽的钱
comes cash, tons of it.

57
00:05:58,930 --> 00:06:01,770
不然你以为我们没事 跑到这沙漠中央干嘛？
What do you think we're doing here in the middle of the desert?

58
00:06:01,850 --> 00:06:03,400
就是为了这些钱
It's all this money.

59
00:06:04,570 --> 00:06:07,320
这是所有炫目的灯光…
This is the end result of all the bright lights...

60
00:06:07,440 --> 00:06:10,480
所有的招待、香槟、免费住宿…
and the comped trips, of all the champagne...

61
00:06:10,610 --> 00:06:14,660
女人与喝不完的酒 最终所造成的结果
and free hotel suites, and all the broads and all the booze.

62
00:06:14,870 --> 00:06:18,910
全都是为了 让我们弄走你的钱
It's all been arranged just for us to get your money.

63
00:06:20,580 --> 00:06:22,290
这就是赌城的真面目
That's the truth about Las Vegas.

64
00:06:24,340 --> 00:06:25,800
我们是唯一的赢家
We're the only winners.

65
00:06:26,050 --> 00:06:27,960
赌徒们一点机会都没有
The players don't stand a chance.

66
00:06:28,430 --> 00:06:30,630
而他们的钱从赌桌上…
And their cash flows from the tables...

67
00:06:30,760 --> 00:06:33,340
流入我们的收银柜再进入保险笼…
to our boxes through the cage...

68
00:06:33,470 --> 00:06:36,340
最后流入全赌场最神圣的房间
and into the most sacred room in the casino.

69
00:06:37,230 --> 00:06:39,470
他们计算钱的地方…
The place where they add up all the money...

70
00:06:39,560 --> 00:06:42,140
注意-请勿进入 万物之首，计算室
the Holy of holies, the count room.

71
00:06:44,820 --> 00:06:46,730
这儿可不是闲杂人等可进出的
Now, this place was off-limits.

72
00:06:47,410 --> 00:06:48,780
连我都进不去
Even I couldn't get inside.

73
00:06:48,870 --> 00:06:51,780
当然，但我的工作是让它保持 满满的状态
But it was my job to keep it filled with cash. That's for sure.

74
00:06:51,910 --> 00:06:53,950
里头的钱多到…
NICKY: They had so much money in there...

75
00:06:54,080 --> 00:06:56,650
可让你用百元大钞砌栋房子
you could build a house out of stacks of $100 bills.

76
00:06:56,750 --> 00:06:58,460
最棒的是…
And the best part was that upstairs...

77
00:06:58,590 --> 00:07:01,540
上头董事会什么屁都不知道
the Board of Directors didn't know what the fuck was going on.

78
00:07:01,710 --> 00:07:03,920
在他们看来一切都干净俐落 没人动手脚
To them everything looked on the up-and-up.

79
00:07:04,050 --> 00:07:05,540
不是吗？当然不
Right? Wrong.

80
00:07:05,680 --> 00:07:06,880
确认五千元
Verify $5,000.

81
00:07:06,970 --> 00:07:08,680
在计算室的那些人…
NICKY: The guys in the counting room...

82
00:07:09,010 --> 00:07:12,350
都是被派进去将里头吸干的
were all slipped in there to skim the joint dry.

83
00:07:12,850 --> 00:07:15,430
他们会少算钱，将计单弄掉
They'd do short counts, they'd lose fill slips.

84
00:07:15,560 --> 00:07:18,020
甚至直接从箱里拿走现款
They'd even take cash right out of the drop-boxes.

85
00:07:18,150 --> 00:07:19,980
全是靠这家伙…
And it was up to this guy right here...

86
00:07:20,110 --> 00:07:22,270
站在两百万元前的这位…
standing in front of $2 million...

87
00:07:22,360 --> 00:07:25,610
在被国税局或任何人发现前…
to skim the cash off the top without anybody getting wise...

88
00:07:25,740 --> 00:07:27,490
把钱摸走
the IRS or anybody.

89
00:07:28,040 --> 00:07:31,160
在计算室里 好像都没人在看
Notice how in the count room nobody ever seems to see anything.

90
00:07:31,290 --> 00:07:33,530
不知怎的，大家都视若无睹
Somehow, somebody's always looking the other way.

91
00:07:33,630 --> 00:07:35,830
看看这些家伙 他们看来真忙，不是吗？
Look at these guys. They look busy, right?

92
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:38,380
他们在算钱，谁会吵他们呢？
They're counting money. Who wants to bother them?

93
00:07:38,550 --> 00:07:41,800
我的意思是，天晓得他们会不会 犯了错而忘记偷钱
I mean, God forbid they should make a mistake and forget to steal.

94
00:07:42,140 --> 00:07:44,670
这期间，你可来去自如
Meanwhile, you're in and you're out.

95
00:07:45,810 --> 00:07:48,590
走过那些鸟事不干的警卫 每礼拜还多拿一百元…
Past the jag-off guard who gets an extra $100 a week...

96
00:07:48,730 --> 00:07:50,100
只为了看门
just to watch the door.

97
00:07:50,480 --> 00:07:53,020
一如往常一样规律…
It's routine. Business as usual...

98
00:07:53,150 --> 00:07:55,850
走进、走出、你好、再见
in, out, hello, goodbye.

99
00:07:55,990 --> 00:07:57,360
就这么简单
That's all there is to it.

100
00:07:57,450 --> 00:08:01,030
就只是个拎着皮箱 走出赌场的肥猪
Just another fat fuck walking out of a casino with a suitcase.

101
00:08:02,240 --> 00:08:04,780
但那口箱子 会直接送往一个地方
Now, that suitcase was going straight to one place:

102
00:08:04,910 --> 00:08:07,620
堪萨斯市，那里是…
right to Kansas City, which was as close...

103
00:08:07,750 --> 00:08:09,990
中部的老大能离拉斯维加斯 最近的地方…
to Las Vegas as the Midwest bosses could go...

104
00:08:10,130 --> 00:08:12,000
而不用怕被逮捕
without getting themselves arrested.

105
00:08:12,960 --> 00:08:16,250
堪萨斯市 老大们要的只是那口箱子
That suitcase was all the bosses ever wanted.

106
00:08:16,340 --> 00:08:18,880
每个月都要
And they wanted it every month.

107
00:08:19,890 --> 00:08:21,760
圣马利诺意大利超市

108
00:08:24,440 --> 00:08:26,390
这个摩门教的混蛋…
Now this old Mormon fuck here...

109
00:08:26,520 --> 00:08:29,860
他每个月都得拿着箱子飞来
he had to fly in with suitcases once a month, nice and easy.

110
00:08:30,190 --> 00:08:32,770
-什么东西这么香？ -他们做了好料的
-Something smells good. -They made us something to eat.

111
00:08:32,900 --> 00:08:34,780
老大们会从各地飞来…
NICKY: The bosses would come from all over:

112
00:08:35,200 --> 00:08:37,400
底特律、克里夫兰、密尔瓦基…
Detroit, Cleveland, Milwaukee...

113
00:08:37,530 --> 00:08:38,910
整个中西部…
all over the Midwest...

114
00:08:39,540 --> 00:08:42,410
他们都会在这个位于 堪萨斯市的市场碰面
and they would meet in this produce market in Kansas City.

115
00:08:42,540 --> 00:08:44,000
根本没人会知道
Nobody even knew it.

116
00:08:44,710 --> 00:08:46,830
有一个让他妈做菜
One of the guys made his mother do the cooking.

117
00:08:46,960 --> 00:08:49,000
你有看到杰瑞史塔瑞欧吗？
Do you ever see that guy Jerry Steriano?

118
00:08:49,260 --> 00:08:51,750
这些老头们看来可能不怎么样
NICKY: These old greaseballs might not look it...

119
00:08:51,880 --> 00:08:53,080
但相信我…
but believe me...

120
00:08:53,220 --> 00:08:56,140
他们才是赌城的秘密操纵者
these are the guys who secretly controlled Las Vegas.

121
00:08:56,260 --> 00:08:57,810
妈妈，那男人又来了
WOMAN: Mama, that man's here again.

122
00:08:57,970 --> 00:09:00,300
因为他们控制着 全美卡车司机工会
NICKY: Because they controlled the Teamsters Union.

123
00:09:00,440 --> 00:09:03,770
而要开赌场非得到那儿去借钱
And that's where you had to go to borrow money to buy a casino.

124
00:09:03,900 --> 00:09:05,770
-你要放虾吗？ -我会的
WOMAN 2: Would you put in shrimp? WOMAN: I would.

125
00:09:06,400 --> 00:09:10,100
要是这些家伙们每月拿不到 这只小箱子…
NICKY: Nobody got a Teamsters' loan unless the guys in this room...

126
00:09:10,200 --> 00:09:12,520
那谁就都别想贷到款
knew they were gonna get their little suitcases.

127
00:09:13,830 --> 00:09:16,320
像这从底特律来的老家伙
Guys like this antique over here, out of Detroit.

128
00:09:18,410 --> 00:09:21,870
或尤其是像利蒙盖吉 这群人的首脑
Or especially guys like Remo Gaggi, the outfit's top boss.

129
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:23,250
有大概数字吗？
You got a round figure on it?

130
00:09:23,380 --> 00:09:25,500
绝对是这房里最重要的人物
NICKY: Definitely the most important guy in this room.

131
00:09:25,590 --> 00:09:29,340
-十公斤，那就差不多七十万了 -很好
FRANK: About 20 pounds. Around $700,000. REMO: Good.

132
00:09:29,800 --> 00:09:32,380
虽说对拉斯维加斯还有点早…
STONE: It's a little early for Las Vegas...

133
00:09:33,470 --> 00:09:37,220
但我想邀请赌博游乐业界的 先生与小姐们…
but I want to welcome the ladies and gentlemen of the gaming industry....

134
00:09:37,520 --> 00:09:39,390
就以世界所知…
SAM: As far as the world was concerned...

135
00:09:39,520 --> 00:09:42,560
安迪史东卡车司机工会 退休基金会的负责人…
Andy Stone, head of the Teamsters' Pension Fund...

136
00:09:42,820 --> 00:09:44,360
是个清白的人物
was a legitimate guy.

137
00:09:45,110 --> 00:09:46,390
有权力的人
A powerful man.

138
00:09:47,450 --> 00:09:49,030
他与总统一同打高尔夫
He played golf with the President.

139
00:09:49,280 --> 00:09:51,410
代表卡车司机工会退休基金会…
ANDY: On behalf of the Teamsters' Pension Fund...

140
00:09:51,540 --> 00:09:54,240
-我很高兴将这… -但安迪也听命于人
I'm glad to present... SAM: But he also took orders.

141
00:09:54,540 --> 00:09:57,620
当他被指示将基金贷款 贷给菲立浦葛林…
When he was told to give a pension-fund loan to Philip Green...

142
00:09:57,750 --> 00:10:00,790
六千两百七十万的支票…
...this check for $62,700,000...

143
00:10:00,920 --> 00:10:02,300
给全新的坦吉乐
for the new Tangiers.

144
00:10:02,880 --> 00:10:04,420
他就会乖乖听话
...he did what he was told.

145
00:10:04,840 --> 00:10:06,550
他可是最完美的傀儡
NICKY: Here was the perfect front man.

146
00:10:06,720 --> 00:10:09,260
他还能干嘛呢？ 他什么都不知道
What the fuck else could he be? He didn't know too much.

147
00:10:09,350 --> 00:10:10,840
也什么都不想知道…
He didn't want to know too much...

148
00:10:10,980 --> 00:10:13,760
尤其是老大们让工会借钱给他
especially that the bosses made the Teamsters lend him money.

149
00:10:13,850 --> 00:10:16,970
他想相信他们是因为 他的才智贷款给他
He wanted to believe they gave him the money because he was smart.

150
00:10:17,320 --> 00:10:20,600
我了解这城市的竞争性有多大 才会说出此话
I say that knowing just how much competition we have in this city.

151
00:10:24,200 --> 00:10:26,070
他们从哪儿找来葛林的？
NICKY: And where they got Green from?

152
00:10:26,410 --> 00:10:27,740
谁知道啊？
Who the fuck knows?

153
00:10:28,000 --> 00:10:30,780
我只知道他在亚利桑那州 是个房地产经纪…
All I know is that he was an Arizona real-estate hustler...

154
00:10:30,870 --> 00:10:34,410
却连开来拿支票的油钱 都差点付不出来
who barely had enough gas money to come and pick up his fucking check.

155
00:10:35,210 --> 00:10:37,090
美国中部 卡车司机工会退休基金 是由老大的人…
And it was the bosses' man...

156
00:10:37,170 --> 00:10:38,960
安迪史东下所有的命令
Andy Stone, who gave all the orders.

157
00:10:39,090 --> 00:10:41,460
并不是由董事会主席 菲立浦葛林
Not the Chairman of the Board, Philip Green.

158
00:10:41,590 --> 00:10:43,470
我了解
I understand.

159
00:10:47,770 --> 00:10:48,970
现在只缺…
NICKY: Now all they needed was...

160
00:10:49,060 --> 00:10:51,180
一个可信任的人来管理赌场
